 698:src/voice.h   **** // ŌöĆŌöĆ Voice 10: snare (noise-driven) ŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌ
 699:src/voice.h   **** //   The bright, noisy cousin of the Tom ŌĆö PLAY IT BY TAPPING. Broadband noise
 700:src/voice.h   **** //   (the "wires" rattle) dominates over two tonal modes (body + a 1.8├Ś ring); a
 701:src/voice.h   **** //   wide-open filter keeps it crisp and cracking. Instant attack, short tail,
 702:src/voice.h   **** //   and a quick subtle pitch snap (0.7 oct in 30 ms) for the hit. Harder presses
 703:src/voice.h   **** //   open it further. Finger-1 position tunes the drum.
